$ YARN application master

The *application master* is the master process of a → development/Apache/Hadoop/YARN/Application[YARN application].

When an application is started, the application master is contacted by the → development/Apache/Hadoop/YARN/client[client]. The application
master then informs the → development/Apache/Hadoop/YARN/Resource-manager[resource manager] about the requested resources. It then
asks the → development/Apache/Hadoop/YARN/Node-manager[node managers] to create the → development/Apache/Hadoop/YARN/container[containers].

The application master is actually just a → development/Apache/Hadoop/YARN/container[container] that was created by the → development/Apache/Hadoop/YARN/Resource-manager[resource manager].
